3.8		We recommended that management:
Support the utilization of QRF with the necessary documents such as resolution of the sanggunian declaring the LGU under the state of calamity and other related documents such as MDRRMC resolution/report of the actual affected areas, the number of family affected, and the extent of damage to justify claims in terms of quantity procured for the distribution of food subsistence/relief goods and other assistance;
Distribute relief goods only to calamity-stricken constituents;
Issue RIS at once for relief goods that were issued and conduct year-end inventory; and
adjust the understated 2016 special trust fund.

We recommended that management:

Demand those who are indebted to the MFT program to immediately settle their overdue accounts;
Deposit the existing cash on hand including the collections from settled accounts to the Trust Fund account;
Search for a qualified person or group who shall manage and operate the MFT program; and
Enter into a MOA with the chosen qualified person or group.
